Abdomen: black with blue sheen, brighter strongly light-reflecting bands on margin of each tergite; admixture of white scales ventrally; anal tuft very small, black. Male genitalia (Fig. 4): tegumen broad proximally, gradually tapered towards uncus; saccus short with broad, slightly bifurcate base; valva broadening from 1/3 length, margins densely covered with long setae, sparser hair-like setae medially; 
uncus
with ring of brown setae; gnathos narrow, long, pointed distally; aedeagus about 1.5 length of valva.
